The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Two men were arrested on Friday for allegedly murdering a 35-year-old woman, Anita, on September 24. Shyamal Halder and his brother-in-law Biplab Roy were picked up from their houses in Kalyani and Dum Dum. Police said Shyamal, a marble stone craftsman, had an affair with Anita, who lived in Dum Dum with her two children. She had been living separately from her husband for the past few years, said an officer.  hyamal allegedly strangled Anita as she had been blackmailing him by threatening to inform his family about the affair. The police said that on September 24 Anita and Shyamal had gone to Biplabs house in Durganagar, where the woman was killed. Neighbours spotted the body in a pond and called the cops.    A 46-year-old man was arrested at a hotel in Shyampur, Howrah, on the charge of killing Manasa Kotal, who had been missing since September 27. Ganesh Gupta, a resident of Bankra, was remanded in police custody for six days on Thursday. The body of the 50-year-old mason was found in a pond near Balitikuri ESI Hospital on September 29. Kotals son lodged a complaint that Gupta had told him that a local youth had shot his father from Guptas revolver.    Kalyan Mitra, a teacher of City College of Commerce and Business Administration, has been missing since Thursday afternoon. His wife lodged a complaint with Uttarpara police station on Friday. Mitra, a philatelist by hobby, had left his Deshbandhu Park home telling his wife that he would sell stamps to someone in Baguiati.    Some members of a swimming club in the Lake area fell ill after chlorine gas leaked from a water treatment plant on the club premises on Friday. Firemen plugged the leak.    Mujibar Rahaman, a 42-year-old tailor, was found dead near his shop in Mahestala on Friday. Residents said Rahaman was last seen quarrelling with Nazrul, another tailor, on Thursday night.                                                                                                                                                                   
